<subSubSection pageId="51" pageNumber="52" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="51.[123,652,193,803]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">
COMMENTS: This is the only specimen of 
<taxonomicName box="[123,272,399,422]" class="Aves" family="Turdidae" genus="Turdus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="colombianus">
<emphasis box="[123,272,399,422]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">colombianus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
that came to AMNH with the Rothschild Collection and it bears a Rothschild 
<typeStatus box="[193,243,457,480]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">type</typeStatus>
label. 
<bibRefCitation author="Hartert, E." box="[330,567,457,480]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" pagination="425 - 505" refId="ref96767" refString="Hartert, E. 1920. Types of birds in the Tring Museum. B. Types in the general collection (contd.). Novitates Zoologicae 27: 425 - 505." type="journal article" year="1920">Hartert (1920: 475)</bibRefCitation>
, in his list of Rothschild 
<typeStatus box="[346,410,486,509]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">types</typeStatus>
, added Rosenberg’s ‘‘no. 1’’ and corrected the year of collection to 1894 without comment. 
<bibRefCitation author="Hartert, E. &amp; C. E. Hellmayr" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" pagination="492 - 493" refId="ref97224" refString="Hartert, E., and C. E. Hellmayr. 1901. On two new thrushes from western Colombia. Novitates Zoologicae 8: 492 - 493." type="journal article" year="1901">Hartert and Hellmayr (1901: 493)</bibRefCitation>
provisionally assigned a specimen collected by Stolzmann at Chimbo, N. 
<collectingCountry box="[161,259,633,656]" name="Ecuador" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
, to 
<taxonomicName box="[305,487,633,656]" class="Aves" family="Turdidae" genus="Turdus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="colombianus">
<emphasis box="[305,487,633,656]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">T. colombianus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="51.[123,652,193,803]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">
<bibRefCitation author="Ripley, S. D." box="[152,390,662,685]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" pagination="13 - 227" refId="ref102558" refString="Ripley, S. D. 1964. Family Muscicapidae. Subfamily Turdinae. In E. Mayr and R. A. Paynter, Jr. (editors), Check-list of birds of the world, vol. 10: 13 - 227. Cambridge, MA: Museum of Comparative Zoology, 502 pp." type="book chapter" year="1964">Ripley (1964: 219)</bibRefCitation>
considered 
<taxonomicName class="Aves" family="Turdidae" genus="Turdus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="colombianus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">colombianus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to be a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lawrence" authorityYear="1869" box="[440,584,692,715]" class="Aves" family="Turdidae" genus="Turdus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="hauxwelli">
<emphasis box="[440,584,692,715]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">T. hauxwelli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Ridgely, R. S. &amp; G. Tudor" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" refId="ref102474" refString="Ridgely, R. S., and G. Tudor. 1989. The birds of South America. Vol. 1. The oscine passerines. Austin: University of Texas Press, 516 pp." type="book" year="1989">Ridgely and Tudor (1989: 125)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Clement, P." pageId="51" pageNumber="52" refId="ref91910" refString="Clement, P. 2000. Thrushes. Princeton, NJ: Princeton University Press, 463 pp." type="book" year="2000">Clement (2000: 424–425)</bibRefCitation>
placed it as a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lawrence" authorityYear="1862" box="[123,266,780,803]" class="Aves" family="Turdidae" genus="Turdus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="obsoletus">
<emphasis box="[123,266,780,803]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">T. obsoletus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
